condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Accountant and accounting software | Description :The Recipient shall, not later than four (4) months after theEffective Date: (i) employ an accountant and an external auditor for the PIU under terms of reference satisfactory and withqualifications and experience satisfactory to the Association; and (ii) finalize the installation of an accounting software for theProject satisfactory to the Association. | Due Date :30-Dec-2013

Finance Agreement :Capacity Purchase contract | Description :The Recipient shall cause the SPV or the PPP, as the case may be, toexecute a capacity purchase contract), in form and substance satisfactory to the Association and in accordance with the PPPprinciples, with a suitable supplier of international bandwidth. | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :Contribution to PIU operating costs | Description :The Recipient shall provide to PIU adequate office space outof charge and the resources necessary to enable the PIU to carry out its responsibilities by means of punctual deposits (A) notlater than 6/30/13, an amount of not less than MRO 12 m; (B) not later than 9/30/13, an amount of not less than MRO 36 m; and (C)not later than 5/31 each year until 2017, an amount of not less than MRO 48m. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Counterpart funding ICT Strategy | Description :The Recipient shall take all action required on its behalf tomake available to the PIU, not later than January 1, 2014, an amount equivalent to at least one million dollars ($1,000,000) tosupport the implementation of activities No. 433 and No. 435 of the 2012-2016 Strategy for ICT and Modernization of Public Service.| Due Date :01-Jan-2014

Finance Agreement :Deadline for the effectiveness of the Co-financing Agreement | Description :The Co-financing Deadline for theeffectiveness of the EIB Co-financing Agreement is December 31, 2014. | Due Date :31-Dec-2014

Finance Agreement :Delegated Contractual Agreement | Description :The Recipient shall cause the Holding Company for Digital Assetsto enter into a delegated contractual agreement with the IMT whereby the Holding Company for Digital Assets shall assign to theIMTfull responsibility for the management and operation of the backbone links and the Internet Exchange Point/CarrierHotel/Datacenter technical building to be built under Part 1 (a) of the Project. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Draft new legislation | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that draft new legislation, satisfactory to theAssociation, aimed to revise the Recipient’s existing ICT legal and regulatory framework is approved by the Recipient’s Council ofMinister not later than September 30, 2013. | Due Date :30-Sep-2013

Finance Agreement :Financial management | Description :The Recipient shall: (i) not later than three (3) months after the EffectiveDate, acquire and install in the PIU accounting software suitable for the purposes of the Project; and (ii) not later than four (4)months after the Effective Date, employ an external auditor for the PIU under terms of reference satisfactory and withqualifications and experience satisfactory to the Association. | Due Date :01-Dec-2014

Finance Agreement :Institutional Arrangements- Recruitment of M&E and Technical Specialist | Description :The Recipient shall, notlater than three (3) months after the Effective Date, employ a monitoring and evaluation specialist, and a telecommunicationsspecialist for the PIU under terms of reference and with qualifications and experience satisfactory to the Association. | Due Date:30-Jun-2014

Finance Agreement :Main Contractual Agreement | Description :The Recipient shall conclude a contractual agreement with the HoldingCompany whereby the Recipient shall, transfer to the Holding Company: (A) on a non-reimbursable basis, the proceeds of theFinancingallocated to Category (1) (a) to finance the building of thebackbone links and the technical building ; and (B) theownership of the backbone links and the technical building. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Main Contractual Agreement | Description :The Recipient shall conclude a contractual agreement with the SPV totransfer to the SPV: (A) on a non-reimbursable basis, the proceeds of the Financing allocated to Category (1) to finance theCarrier Hotel and (B) the ownership of the Carrier Hotel to be established under of the Project. | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :National Connectivity Steering Commission | Description :The Recipient shall maintain throughout Projectimplementation the National Connectivity Steering Commission under terms of reference satisfactory to the Association and vestedwith the responsibility of providing overall technical and operative guidance, direction and coordination during Projectimplementation. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Safeguards Compliance | Description :Recipient shall:(i) take all measures required to carry out, and to ensurethat the SPV and/or the PPP, carry out, the ESIA, ESMP, and/or the RAP, in accordance with the provisions of the ESMF and RPF;(ii)ensure that relevant mitigation and monitoring are appropriately implemented and that information on how potential negativeimpact has been minimized is suitably included in the Project Reports. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Safeguards compliance | Description :Recipient shall take & ensure the Holding Company take all action necessary(i) to comply with the ESMF & RPF and to carry out the ESIA and/or the ESMP & RAP; (ii) to ensure that relevant mitigation &monitoring provisions of safeguards instruments are appropriately included in works, goods & services contracts under Part 1(a);(iii) to maintain Recipient & IDA suitably informed of implementation. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Site of the Internet Exchange Point/technical building | Description :The Recipient shall make available to theHolding Company for Digital Assets, in the form of in-kind contribution and free of charge, the piece of land suitable andnecessaryfor the building of the said Internet Exchange Point/Carrier Hotel/Datacenter technical building, both in size and legaland physical condition acceptable to the Association. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Training | Description :For the purposes of the Training to be provided under the Project, the Recipientshall:a)furnish to the Association for its approval, not later than January 31 of each year, a training;b)select the trainees inaccordance with a transparent process and criteria satisfactory to the Association; c)furnish to the Association a report on theresults of each training. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Training | Description :The Recipient shall furnish to the Association for its approval, not later than November30 of each year, a training program, and shall select the trainees in accordance with a transparent process and criteriasatisfactory to the Association. | Frequency :Yearly

The Recipient shall cause the SPV to enter into a PPP agreement with the PPP whereby the SPV shall assign to the PPP responsibilityfor the management and operation of the Carrier Hotel established under the project. | Due date: November 15, 2020

The Recipient shall: (i) not later than three (3) months after the Effective Date, acquire and install in the PIU accountingsoftware suitable for the purposes of the Project; and (ii) not later than four (4) months after the Effective Date, employ anexternal auditor for the PIU under terms of reference satisfactory and with qualifications and experience satisfactory to theAssociation.
